# Site Name

> Short public description of the site, audience, and what information is authoritative here.

## Core Pages

- [Home](https://example.com/): Primary overview and current positioning.
- [Products](https://example.com/products/): Canonical product or service catalog.
- [Pricing](https://example.com/pricing/): Current pricing model, plans, limits, and terms.
- [Documentation](https://example.com/docs/): Public docs and API guidance.
- [Support](https://example.com/support/): Support paths, contact options, and policies.

## Policies

- [Terms](https://example.com/terms/): Terms of service.
- [Privacy](https://example.com/privacy/): Privacy policy.
- [Security](https://example.com/security/): Security posture and disclosure path.

## Optional

- [Changelog](https://example.com/changelog/): Product changes and release dates.
- [API Reference](https://example.com/api/): Public API reference or OpenAPI documentation.
